Juvenile colouration in life.
(based on tank-raised juveniles of approximately 
20 to 30 mm
SL; 
Fig. 9
). Ground colouration greyish to beige. Patterns and head mask as described for adults. No reddish speckles present. Dorsal and midlateral band, greyish vertical bars on flank as described for adults. Dorsal fin hyaline to beige with vertical flank bars extending onto fin. Anal, caudal, pectoral and pelvic fin hyaline.
